005package edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command;
006
007/**
008 * A {@link TimedCommand} will wait for a timeout before finishing. {@link TimedCommand} is used to
009 * execute a command for a given amount of time.
010 *
011 * <p>This class is provided by the OldCommands VendorDep
012 */
013public class TimedCommand extends Command {
014  /**
015   * Instantiates a TimedCommand with the given name and timeout.
016   *
017   * @param name the name of the command
018   * @param timeout the time the command takes to run (seconds)
019   */
020  public TimedCommand(String name, double timeout) {
021    super(name, timeout);
022  }
023
024  /**
025   * Instantiates a TimedCommand with the given timeout.
026   *
027   * @param timeout the time the command takes to run (seconds)
028   */
029  public TimedCommand(double timeout) {
030    super(timeout);
031  }
032
033  /**
034   * Instantiates a TimedCommand with the given name and timeout.
035   *
036   * @param name the name of the command
037   * @param timeout the time the command takes to run (seconds)
038   * @param subsystem the subsystem that this command requires
039   */
040  public TimedCommand(String name, double timeout, Subsystem subsystem) {
041    super(name, timeout, subsystem);
042  }
043
044  /**
045   * Instantiates a TimedCommand with the given timeout.
046   *
047   * @param timeout the time the command takes to run (seconds)
048   * @param subsystem the subsystem that this command requires
049   */
050  public TimedCommand(double timeout, Subsystem subsystem) {
051    super(timeout, subsystem);
052  }
053
054  /** Ends command when timed out. */
055  @Override
056  protected boolean isFinished() {
057    return isTimedOut();
058  }
059}
